## 14. i18n, Branding & User Content

### 14.1 App Name & Branding

- **App Name:** The app is strictly named **"Finance Tracer"** in English and **"מעקב פיננסי"** in Hebrew. Apply this format everywhere — page titles, headers, footers, metadata, and documentation. The old name "מנהל התקציב שלי" is retired.
- **SSOT owner for app name:** `src/config/app.ts` (`APP_NAME`). All code that needs the app name must import from there.
- Built-in UI strings for the app name are mirrored in `src/i18n/locales/en.json` and `src/i18n/locales/he.json` under the key `app.name`.

### 14.2 Translation Workflow (Built-in UI Strings)

- Any new built-in UI component added to the app **MUST** have its strings translated into both English and Hebrew and added to the core i18n dictionary files (`src/i18n/locales/en.json` and `src/i18n/locales/he.json`) for all users.
- No hardcoded display strings are permitted in components, hooks, or domain code. All UI copy must use `t('key')` from `react-i18next`.
- **SSOT owners:** `src/i18n/locales/en.json` (English UI strings), `src/i18n/locales/he.json` (Hebrew UI strings), `src/i18n/index.ts` (init + `changeLanguage`).

### 14.3 Dynamic User Content Translation

- When a user creates a custom item (e.g., a custom category or expense description), the app **MUST** automatically call the Translation API to translate the item into the opposite language. Both the original and translated versions must be saved together as a `BilingualText` object (`src/types/bilingual.ts`).
- The **only** approved entry point for creating `BilingualText` from user input via the API is `src/services/translation/createBilingualText.ts`.
- Translation errors must surface as visible UI errors — never silently swallowed. Do not save partial data (only original, no translation) without explicit user acknowledgement.
- **SSOT owner for Translation API IO:** `src/services/translation/translationService.ts` (MyMemory API).

### 14.4 Storage of User Content

- User-generated items and their dynamic translations must be saved in **Firebase Firestore** for authenticated users (path: `users/{uid}/categories`), or in **`localStorage`** for guest users (key: `customCategories`).
- The branching between guest and authenticated storage is owned exclusively by each repository module (e.g., `src/services/categories/categoryRepository.ts`). No hook or component may branch on auth state for storage purposes.
- Auth state is obtained via `src/services/auth/authSessionService.ts` and exposed reactively via `src/features/auth/hooks/useAuthSession.ts`.

### 14.5 Bilingual Data Model

- Every piece of user-entered text that will be displayed in the UI **must** be stored as `BilingualText { en: string; he: string }`, never as a plain string.
- Display of `BilingualText` always goes through `src/domain/i18n/resolveBilingualText.ts` — no inline bracket access (`text[locale]`) in components.
- Legacy plain-string data (expense descriptions, category names) is migrated to `BilingualText` at load time via `wrapLegacyText` in `src/domain/i18n/buildBilingualText.ts`.

### 14.6 Category IDs (SSOT)

- Built-in category persistence keys are stable English IDs (`food`, `health`, `entertainment`, `rent`, `other`) — never localized display strings.
- Display labels for built-in categories come from i18n: `t('category.food')` etc.
- Legacy Hebrew category strings stored in old localStorage data are migrated to IDs at load time via `migrateCategoryId` in `src/domain/categories/constants.ts`.

### 14.7 SSOT Registry for i18n & User Content

| Responsibility | Owner |
|---|---|
| App name (en/he) | `src/config/app.ts` + `src/i18n/locales/*.json` key `app.name` |
| Built-in English UI strings | `src/i18n/locales/en.json` |
| Built-in Hebrew UI strings | `src/i18n/locales/he.json` |
| i18n init + language change | `src/i18n/index.ts` |
| Locale preference persistence | `src/i18n/index.ts` (`localStorage` key `locale`) |
| Document lang/dir sync | `src/app/providers/I18nProvider.tsx` |
| Language toggle component | `src/features/i18n/components/LanguageToggle.tsx` |
| Translation API IO (MyMemory) | `src/services/translation/translationService.ts` |
| BilingualText creation from user input | `src/services/translation/createBilingualText.ts` |
| Bilingual text shape | `src/types/bilingual.ts` |
| Display resolution (BilingualText → string) | `src/domain/i18n/resolveBilingualText.ts` |
| Build BilingualText from parts | `src/domain/i18n/buildBilingualText.ts` |
| Legacy text migration | `src/domain/i18n/buildBilingualText.ts` (`wrapLegacyText`) |
| Built-in category IDs + legacy migration | `src/domain/categories/constants.ts` |
| Category label resolution | `src/domain/categories/resolveCategoryLabel.ts` |
| Custom category type | `src/types/category.ts` |
| Custom category persistence (guest + auth) | `src/services/categories/categoryRepository.ts` |
| Custom category feature hook | `src/features/categories/hooks/useCategories.ts` |
| Auth session IO | `src/services/auth/authSessionService.ts` |
| Auth session React hook | `src/features/auth/hooks/useAuthSession.ts` |
| Date/number locale formatting | `src/lib/format/formatDate.ts` |
| Date picker / calendar UI (all app date selection) | `src/components/calendar/CustomDatePicker.tsx` |

### 14.8 i18n Red Flags — Stop Immediately

| Thought | Reality |
|---|---|
| "I'll hardcode a display string in Hebrew or English in JSX" | Add the key to both locale JSON files and use `t('key')`. |
| "The category name is always Hebrew so I'll compare it to a string" | Use stable ID comparisons. Hebrew category strings are display-only. |
| "I'll save the translation later and just store the original now" | Both languages must be persisted atomically — see 14.3. |
| "I'll call `translateText` directly in the component" | Route through `createBilingualText.ts` → `useCategories` or `useBudgetTracker`. |
| "The user is authenticated so I'll write to Firestore from the hook" | Firestore writes belong in the repository. Hooks call repositories. |
| "I'll add the app name as a string constant here" | Import from `src/config/app.ts`. |

### 14.9 Pre-Submit Additions for i18n Changes

- [ ] Every new UI string has a key in **both** `en.json` and `he.json`.
- [ ] No `t()` calls reference keys that don't exist in both locale files.
- [ ] User-created content creates `BilingualText` via `createBilingualText.ts`.
- [ ] Translation failures surface as visible errors; no silent fallbacks.
- [ ] App name displayed as "Finance Tracer" (en) / "מעקב פיננסי" (he) everywhere.
- [ ] Category persistence uses stable IDs, not display strings.

---

## 15. Numeric Input Scroll Wheel

Whenever creating or editing numeric input fields (e.g., `<input type="number">` or custom number input components), the AI must ALWAYS write code that disables the mouse scroll wheel from changing the input's value (e.g., by blurring the input on scroll or using an appropriate event preventer in React).

### 15.1 SSOT owner

| Responsibility | Owner |
|---|---|
| Scroll-wheel prevention handler for number inputs | `src/lib/input/preventNumberInputScroll.ts` |

All `type="number"` inputs must use `onWheel={preventNumberInputScroll}` from this module — no inline duplicates, no global document listeners.

### 15.2 Pre-Submit Additions for Numeric Inputs

- [ ] Every `type="number"` input uses `preventNumberInputScroll` from `src/lib/input/preventNumberInputScroll.ts`.
- [ ] No ad-hoc `onWheel` handlers for number inputs at call sites.

---

## 16. Date Picker — CustomDatePicker Only

Whenever the app needs date selection or a calendar interface, the AI must **strictly** use the global `CustomDatePicker` component. Native and third-party date pickers are forbidden.

### 16.1 SSOT owner

| Responsibility | Owner |
|---|---|
| Date picker modal UI (all app date selection) | `src/components/calendar/CustomDatePicker.tsx` |
| Public import surface | `src/components/calendar/index.ts` |
| Calendar grid generation | `src/components/calendar/buildCalendarGrid.ts` |
| Calendar built-in UI strings | `src/i18n/locales/en.json` + `src/i18n/locales/he.json` keys under `calendar.*` |

All date selection must import `{ CustomDatePicker } from 'src/components/calendar'` (or relative equivalent). Wire a trigger button/field in the feature component; open the modal with `open` / `value` / `onConfirm` / `onCancel`.

**Forbidden at call sites:** `<input type="date">`, native browser date pickers, third-party date/calendar libraries.

### 16.2 Red flags — stop immediately

| Thought | Reality |
|---|---|
| "I'll use type=\"date\" for a quick date field" | Use `CustomDatePicker` from `src/components/calendar`. |
| "I'll add react-datepicker for this screen" | Use `CustomDatePicker` — one visual language app-wide. |
| "I'll duplicate the calendar modal in this feature" | Extend or reuse `CustomDatePicker`; do not fork the UI. |

### 16.3 Pre-Submit Additions for Date Selection

- [ ] No `type="date"` inputs anywhere in the codebase.
- [ ] All date-selection flows import `CustomDatePicker` from `src/components/calendar`.
- [ ] New calendar UI strings use `calendar.*` keys in both locale files.

---

